parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed camera affects safety-related functionality, putting the driver and other drivers at risk.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights on the dash
including road departure mitigation system
adaptive cruise control
lane keeping assist
auto high beam warning
and collision mitigation system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalls in the middle of traffic, causing a safety hazard, and may lead to accidents or rear-ending.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when stopped at a red traffic light
and the idle stop feature fails to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The system failure causes a distraction to the driver, and the loss of safety features such as backup camera, lane notifications, and GPS.
symptoms: The infotainment system freezes or goes completely out
making a loud noise or crackling sound
and losing all additional safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The latch failure causes the door to open while driving, leading to a safety hazard, and may cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear door latch breaks
causing the door to open while driving
and the door may not close or lock properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction causes the door to open or close unexpectedly, leading to a safety hazard, and may cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The sliding door opens or closes unexpectedly
and may not respond to commands
causing a safety hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure causes the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a safety hazard, and may cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission fails
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power
and may display a warning message on the screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The backup camera failure reduces safety when reversing, and may cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a system failure message
and may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal sound indicator may cause the driver to forget to turn off the signal, leading to a safety hazard.
symptoms: The turn signal sound indicator is not audible
and may be drowned out by engine noise
open windows
or radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Crackling Noise from Front Windshield or Dash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The crackling noise may be a distraction to the driver, and may indicate a underlying electrical or mechanical issue.
symptoms: A crackling noise is heard from the front windshield or dash area
most frequently when the vehicle is moving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The gaseous odor may be a sign of a underlying issue with the air conditioning or ventilation system, and may cause discomfort or health issues.
symptoms: A gaseous odor permeates the cabin from the air vents
especially when the vehicle is idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Camera Failure Affecting Advanced Driver-Assistance Systems (ADAS)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front camera can cause multiple ADAS systems to malfunction, including adaptive cruise control, lane keeping assist, collision mitigation, road departure mitigation, and auto high-beam, which can lead to accidents or near-misses due to the sudden loss of critical safety features.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
including Adaptive Cruise Control Problem
Lane Keeping Assist Problem
Collision Mitigation System Problem
Road Departure Mitigation System Problem
and Auto High-Beam Problem. The systems may malfunction intermittently or permanently
causing distractions while driving and potentially leading to accidents.
